*Summary*
Expanding "changelog" for JIRA REST API "search" with POST throws error.
{noformat}
{"errorMessages":["Can not deserialize instance of java.util.ArrayList out of VALUE_STRING token\n at [Source: org.apache.catalina.connector.CoyoteInputStream@4bee02; line: 4, column: 18] (through reference chain: com.atlassian.jira.rest.v2.search.SearchRequestBean[\"expand\"])"]} 
{noformat}

JSON sample:
{noformat}
{ "jql": "project=AP", "startAt": 0, "maxResults": 15, "expand": "changelog", "fields": ["summary", "key", "changelog"] }
{noformat}

*Workaround(partial)*
Encode the JQL into URL if possible e.g:
{noformat}
https://<domain>.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/search?jql=project=AP&startAt=0&maxResults=15&fields=summary,key,changelog&expand=changelog
{noformat}

h3. Summary

When calling the REST API endpoint {{/rest/api/2/issue/\{issueIdOrKey}/worklog}} the value set for the parameters startAt and maxResults are ignored.
h3. Environment

JIRA Cloud 1000.773.2
h3. Steps to Reproduce 

Call {{/rest/api/2/issue/\{issueIdOrKey}/worklog}} endpoint passing a value for _startAt_ and/or _maxResults_. E.g. [https://instance|https://instance/]-name.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/12345/worklog?startAt=20&maxResults=20
h3. Expected results

The results shown should start from worklog no 20 and display only the next 20 worklog results. 
{code:java}
{"startAt":20,"maxResults":20,"total":20,"worklogs":
...
}{code}
h3. Actual Results

All the results are shown regardless of the pagination options entered. 
{code:java}
{"startAt":0,"maxResults":55,"total":55,"worklogs":
...
}{code}

h3. Summary
Per [API - Latest: Create USER API | https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/ondemand/#api/2/user-createUser] You can create as many user accounts as you want using the same e-mail.  Only erring is username is already in use.

h3. Environment
* JIRA v7.2.0-OD-05-022
* Tested With POSTMAN and Direct CLI vi curl

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# POST to API endpoint {{https://<INSTANCE_NAME>.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user}}
# BODY:
{code}
{
    "name": "<first_username>",
    "password": "<password>",
    "emailAddress": "<email@example.com>",
    "displayName": "<Full Name>",
	"notification": "true"
}
{code}
# Do a second POST only changing the Username:
{code}
{
    "name": "<second_username>",
    "password": "<password>",
    "emailAddress": "<email@example.com>",
    "displayName": "<Full Name>",
	"notification": "true"
}
{code}

h3. Expected Results
Fail to create Second Account with error:
{code}
{
    "errorMessages": [],
    "errors": {
        "emailAddress": "This email belongs to <first_username>."
    }
}
{code}

h3. Actual Results
User is created causing duplicate accounts
 
h3. Notes
Testing Discovered:
- https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-60454

h3.Workaround
Manually Delete second user per:
- https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/add-edit-and-remove-users-744721624.html
(!) if the user has contributed content or comments on your site, you will not be able to delete them, until the content is also deleted

(This is concerning the [ServiceRocket Salesforce.com Connector Plugin|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/net.customware.plugins.connector.salesforce.salesforce-connector-plugin/server/overview] pre-installed on JIRA Cloud, not the new [Salesforce & JIRA Cloud Connector|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.servicerocket.jira.salesforce/cloud/overview]).

h4. Symptoms

When associating a Salesforce object with a JIRA issue, one or more of these may happen:

* The search box does not yield any search result. Browser console throws error code 400.
* A warning message appears:
{quote}There is no projects bound to this mapping{quote}

h4. Status

{panel}
Fix has been deployed.
{panel}
